HEADWORD: Snaggy
<hw>Snag"gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Full of
snags; full of short, rough branches or sharp points; abounding with
knots.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Upon a <xex>snaggy</xex> oak.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Snappish; cross; ill-tempered.</def> <mark>[Prov.
Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

